  originalLanguage: en
  translationSets:
  - counter: 6
    languageCode: en
    translations:
    - id: 0
      language: en
      text: Georgia
    - id: 1
      language: en
      text: You call that armor? Looks like something my aunt would hang laundry
        on.
    - id: 2
      language: en
      text: "Men say they\u2019re brave until a spider walks across their ale."
    - id: 3
      language: en
      text: These cobblestones do more damage to my feet than any battlefield.
    - id: 4
      language: en
      text: I once saw a raven deliver a message to the castle. Black wings, red
        seal. Gave me chills.
    - id: 5
      language: en
      text: "If I had a coin for every hero claiming to slay dragons, I\u2019d own
        a dragon."
